RARIES AND VILLAGE DEVELOPMENT IN PAPUA NEW GUINEA.ATTEMPTS TO OUTLINE POSSIBLE MODELS FOR LIBRARIES WHICH MIGHT STRENGTHEN THEIRCONTRIBUTION TO THE DEVELOPMENT OF RURAL VILLAGES IN PAPUA NEW GUINEA.DISCUSSES 2 PARTICULAR MODELS-THE LIBRARY EXTENSION MODEL (THE TAKING OFEXISTING LIBRARY SERVICES INTO THE COMMUNITY); AND THE VILLAGE INFORMATIONCENTRE MODEL (AN INFORMATION ORGANISATION LOCATED IN A GEOGRAPHIC AREASPECIFICALLY SET UP TO ASSIST VILLAGERS AND PROFESSIONAL FIELDWORKERS TODEVELOP THAT PARTICULAR GEOGRAPHIC AREA)